From 12ffba7295cca59ed3e76f835489b6ad70ce8bff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nidhi Jain <nidhjain@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Jun 2025 10:27:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add support to handle
TTLM negotiation via association frames

Add support to parse the TTLM element received in the association
request from non-AP MLD and send association response from AP MLD
based on user configured response status code.

If the ttlm_enable flag is enabled, the default response code is
set to accept the STA preference and AP MLD to send the association
response without TTLM element which indicates the TTLM negotiation
success as per Draft P80211.be_D3.0 section 35.3.7.1.3 Negotiation
of Tid-to-link mapping.

If the response status code is configured as reject,then send the
association response with TTLM element having default mapping.

Signed-off-by: Nidhi Jain <nidhjain@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Dhanavandhana Kannan <dhanavan@qti.qualcomm.com>
